                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v04</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1054</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1054</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-04-29T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1054" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1054">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of Defense Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to the
                        British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-29">April 29,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Replying to your Number 19, the Combined Chiefs of Staff in F.A.N. 536, on 28
                    April, with my approval, authorized Alexander to accomplish what I understand to
                    be your idea regarding Trieste and other areas formerly under Italian rule as a
                    matter of military necessity.</p>
                <p>I do not know what the effect of the forthcoming German surrender in Italy may
                    have on Alexander’s plans in this matter.</p>
            </div>
